cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with the capacity of wireless relay networks, which is a problem in information theory and networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves the study of wireless channels and their interactions, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The algorithmic aspect of the paper suggests that it could also be classified under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper uses linear algebraic techniques to solve the problem, which could place it under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
